comment: Aqua-man is literally my fav DC character, and the movie was absolutely amazing. Amber Heard, who portrayed Mera in the movie, played the role with such passion and emotion. She wasn‚Äôt just some sideline female character who got limited screen time. I feel as though Amber Heard brought a sense of female empowerment and strength to her role, and her personal relationship with Jason is great. To be honest, I think Warner Brothers don‚Äôt want him speaking out about the situation, but I never even knew this was happening in the first place. As an actress, Amber plays the role perfectly, and I‚Äôve watched the movie so many times that I can‚Äôt imagine her being replaced at all. I‚Äôm not going to biased and talk about a situation that I barely know about, but to be honest, Amber Heard plays the role of Mera in Aqua-man beautifully, and I think at the end of the day, it‚Äôs the company‚Äôs decision whether or not they feel that she should be removed. She is such a strong and prominent character in this movie, that it would be a shame if she wasn‚Äôt seen in the second film. There‚Äôs always going to be controversy or some sort of scandal revolving around actors and actresses, especially in Hollywood, but I hope that they look at the amazing actress they would be letting go, and not based solely on the scandal revolving around her. JD is an amazing actor, and I think it is best that they get a divorce, but how many times have we seen this type of thing in Hollywood? Couples divorce and go into a full on custody battle, and someone accuses this person of something. We‚Äôve all heard it before, but we also have to think about how the actor or actress performs as well. It seems as though Amber was done a good job with portraying her character, and I think a lot of fans of Aqua man in general agree. Now these are just all opinions, and the people that are signing that petition are not necessarily right in doing so, but that‚Äôs just their own opinions regarding the situation. They talk about siding with Jd over Amber Heard, but there‚Äôs always going to be sides, and none are necessarily right or wrong. As an actress and how she portrays Mera, I feel as though Amber should stay (AS AN ACTRESS).

When the press discovered the arrest, Ms. Heard had *her victim* make a lie filled press release, which was quickly debunked when Officer Beverly Leonard, the arresting officer, came forward to answer Ms. Heard's assertion that she was misogynistic, and homophobic, by clearly stating she is an openly gay woman, and Gay Rights Activist, who donates her time to domestic abuse shelters.  Amber Heard should never have been hired for the role of Mera in the first place.  She is a domestic abuser.

comment:
As if destroying Johnny Depp's (JD)  life was not enough for Amber, it seems she has been very involved with Evan Rachel Wood's (ERW) recent allegations against Marilyn Manson (MM).  Prior to this case I was not aware that  JD and MM were very close friends. 
 I started to look into Evan's accusations because I could not figure out how such a kind and gentle man like JD would make a man who burns, cuts and tortures women his beloved daughter's godfather.  What I have learned in the last two or three days is shocking - I now believe there is evidence to prove that Evan and Amber have been colluding for YEARS to frame both JD and MM.  
Evan and MM broke up in 2010 or 2011.  After the split Evan only had great things to say about MM and credited him with giving her a stable home and "room to grow".   Evan and MM kept in close contact with JD the whole time and they were all the best of friends.   At the beginning of 2016 JD started to confess to his friends that he was having a very hard time with Amber but he was afraid to leave her because she was threatening to accuse him of domestic abuse and sexual assaults if he ever left her -  can you imagine the stress?  ERW was well aware of the truth that Amber was herself the abuser, and, in essence,  was planning to  extort JD.   Finally JD had enough and left.  Within one  week Amber went to the courthouse (with a bruise painted on) and had a restraining order put on him.  What happened 5 weeks later?  ERW held a press conference and reported she had been beaten, stabbed, cut and tortured by a domestic partner she did NOT name.   At this point she had been split from MM for over 6 YEARS!  I now think that ERW was blackmailing MM  since then  with the threat she would name him.  
We now know that all of the women accusing MM have been organized - they ALL came out on Feb 1st., the exact same day as ERW. No-one gave any dates or places and never really mention crimes, other than two who said MM cut them for a blood pact.  There is also one police record in 2018 but there were no charges because there was no corroberation and the incident happened over 10 years ago.  I believe ALL of the charges from the nine women are at least that old because he has been with his current wife for over 10 years.  MM has been with 3 different wives/partners for a total of 22 years.  NONE of them were abused.
I believe that this whole thing needs to be investigated as a possible extortion case against both Amber and Evan. Both men have suffered extreme duress and have had their careers destroyed.  Both women, if proven to have set up this criminal extortion, need to go to prison.  They can be a cautionary tale regarding our cancel culture mentality.  Evan  named MM as her abuser on feb 1st.  On Feb. 2nd he lost his record deal, his TV show and his agents at Creative Artists Agency.  This was obviously all pre-arranged with Evan and the 9 women.  THIS MUST STOP.
